## Skittle Trans Nails: How to Wear All Three Colours Without the Full Flag Read

Five shades on five nails looks like a considered colour decision. It does not look like a flag.

The skittle manicure  where each nail wears a different shade  is one of the most effective vehicles for <strong>subtle trans nails</strong> because it distributes the three colours across the hand in a way that registers as editorial rather than symbolic. A traditional trans flag nail set has a repeating pattern that, once you know it, is identifiable. A skittle set in pastel baby blue, powder pink, and cloud white  each nail a different shade in a non-sequential order  reads as a thoughtful, trend-aware manicure.

Execution is simple. Base coat on all nails, then work colour by colour: all the blue nails, then all the pink, then white. Finish with a glossy or matte top coat across all ten. The finish changes the feel significantly: gloss reads warmer and more classic, matte reads cooler and more contemporary, and a jelly finish on all three shades creates a cohesive translucent effect that ties the colours together beautifully.

