## Short Nails, No Problem  Subtle Trans Designs That Work at Any Length

Short nails do not need simplifying. They need editing.

Every design in this guide works on short nails  some of them work better. The accent nail is completely length-agnostic: the ring finger takes the trans colour, the rest take the base, and the proportions work identically at any length. The skittle manicure is similarly length-neutral.

Where short nails require most thought is micro stripe work. Five full horizontal stripes across a very short nail can look crowded. Two or three stripes  one blue, one pink, one white  positioned in the lower half of the nail is the cleaner read. On very short nails, a single thin stripe of each colour at the tip functions as a barely-there micro French version of the trans flag.

Jelly finishes are arguably at their best on short nails. The glassy, translucent quality of a jelly blue or a soap-finish white carries a particularly modern, editorial quality on a short, clean nail shape. Short square or oval nails carry the jelly effect more cleanly than longer almond or coffin shapes, which add visual complexity that competes with the finish.

Negative space designs are the only genuine limitation for very short length  they need nail surface to make the geometric effect read. If your nails are very short, skip negative space and go straight to jelly skittle or accent nail.

